main event: Two star-like objects were observed in the sky over Bellport, Long Island, New York on October 29-30, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were reported as being stationary, although they did not disappear while being watched.
One observer was asked if he could see the object on the star Capella, and he confirmed that he could.
The description of the objects is consistent with an astronomical observation.
The witnesses were described as intelligent, reliable, and credible.
The weather conditions were clear with unlimited ceiling and good visibility.
